We will be developing a learning management system that will have 3 users (admin, teachers, and students)
*Admin 
  ~creates accounts for teachers and students using microsoft entra
    *(accounts should be stored in supabase)
*Teachers 
  --creates class (just like in google classroom)
    >>each class should be named by Name of Subject, Name of the Section, and Semester
    >>just like in google classroom, there should be an invitation code because it was the client's preference to use google classroom as a UX reference; 
      teachers will copy the code then send it to the students (codes can be sent to messenger tho, teachers will just copy them and paste it there)
  --will be the one to upload learning materials such as modules
  --uploads activities and quizzes with due dates that can be connected to the calendar 
  --acquire grades from activities and quizzes (so there should be a gradebook where the grades of the students' activities and quizzes are stored)
    >>activities and quizzes can be automatically checked by the system unless they are essay and needs to be read and manually checked by the teachers
    then they'll just put the score then the system will automatically put it inside the gradebook part once checked
  --send announcements
*Students 
  --joins the class created by the teacher thru codes sent by the teacher
  --will be the one to view/access the uploaded learning materials such as the modules and activities
  --will be the one to submit their activities inside the system
  --takes quizzes


